						               													<description>Principle Dilemma - The righteous pursuit through moral combat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This intellectual card-based board game gives each player the opportunity to use their creative thinking and moral compass to delve deeper into their own minds, thoughts and discomforts as well as those of their opponents. Players will expand their minds by analyzing some realistic and  some not so realistic situations where one is forced to make a moral choice. Some choices may be easy while others may be much more difficult.  Players who engage honestly with an open mind may learn some things about their opponents as well as themselves as they challenge each other in a battle of strategic persuasion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For each round, one person plays the role of the hero while the others play as the tricksters. The hero is faced with a dilemma and must make a moral decision. The tricksters must make use of their cards and their creative mindset to attempt to alter the dilemma in such a way that will cause the hero to change their mind. Those tricksters who can change the hero&amp;rsquo;s mind score a point for the round. The winner of Principle Dilemma is the one who scores the most points in a predetermined number of rounds, or is the first to score a predetermined number of points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This party game for thinkers can be played seriously or just for fun. Either way, it shatters the ice in a meaningful way by providing a stage for authentic and exciting conversation between friends and strangers alike. When the stakes are lifted and the variations eccentric, there is freedom to explore outside the box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
